Crème Rappel
http://hans.fugal.net/src/creme/

Synopsis
--------

    creme 1200 lunchtime
    creme 1710 go catch the bus

Requirements
------------

    - Ruby (included in OS X Tiger and above)
    - Growl
    - growlnotify (distributed with Growl in the Extras folder)

To get at working on launchd systems, see [2]. For more blabbering about Crème
Rappel, see [1].

1. http://hans.fugal.net/blog/articles/2008/02/15/cr%C3%A8me-rappel
2. http://hans.fugal.net/blog/articles/2008/02/13/atd-on-a-mac

Installation
------------

    sudo ruby setup.rb

You may need to symlink or adjust PATH if you're using Leopard's Ruby.

Details
-------

    creme [timespec [message]]

If message is omitted, it is expected on stdin. If both are omitted, then
multiple notifications can be specified, one per line.

Timespecs are compatible with at(1), but more friendly. For example, you can do 
"+5m" instead of "+ 5 minutes".

